==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*wolka-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[wolken]], Old Saxon [[wolkan]] (Dutch [[wolk]] ‘cloud’), Old High German [[wolkan]] (German [[Wolke]] ‘cloud’).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'wolken/

===Noun===
'''wolcen''' ''n'' (''pl'' '''wolcnu''')
# a [[cloud]]; clouds
# the [[sky]], the [[heavens]]

===Descendents===
*English [[welkin]]

